items.name: Yamer Model (Gen 2)
items.description:
Checkpoint Type: Fantasy/Everything/Horror/Anime/Style

Support me on Twitter: @YamerOfficial

Welcome to an extraordinary checkpoint that ignites the flames of creativity, giving birth to mesmerizing and visually captivating images. It surpasses the boundaries of specific genres, granting you the freedom to embark on an artistic odyssey without limits.

Within this realm, I invite you to immerse yourself in the enchanting world of "LoRAs" and harness the power of the "clip skip" technique, which adds an extra spark of brilliance to your creations.

Embrace the boundless realm of experimentation, where your imagination knows no bounds, and witness the unrivaled potential of this checkpoint come to life.

Try it with these modifications! ;3

  • LoRA: A-Mecha Musume, Zinogre, HorrorMultiverse, Biomechanicals

  • Hypernetwork: Metal Outfits, Disco Elysium, Venom Hypernetwork, Pain

  • Sampler: Euler Ancestral, DPM2 Ancestral, Heun

  • Checkpoint tested with: Easy Diffusion v2.5.39

Creator Note: "My quest for improvement knows no bounds, and your input is a precious resource on this journey. So please, don't hesitate to share your thoughts and help me grow and evolve over time. Additionally, if you found the results generated by my checkpoint to be exceptional, I would appreciate a 5-star review! Your support means a lot." :]

My Links: twitter, discord, IG

Subscribe for FBB images @ https://patreon.com/fitCorderAI

fcPortrait now has three variations, the base one, one with a sweaty/heat effect and another that adds detail and vibrancy. You only need to use one per image generation.

Designed to amplify the impact of your visual narratives, fcPortrait seamlessly blends a suite of powerful photography techniques into one game-changing embedding. From the dramatic emphasis of rim lighting to the dreamy allure of a bokeh background, every detail is accounted for. It harnesses the sophistication of a fast shutter speed to freeze motion and a low ISO setting to minimize noise, providing clarity that is second to none. The tool's ability to fill the frame with your subject, coupled with an eye-level angle, ensures a neutral yet compelling perspective. Prepare to elevate your artistry with fcPortrait.

It seems like sd always generates some strappy heels even though we put that in the negative prompt. This is a simple Lora that can potentially remove the ankle strap from the pointed-toe heels when the weight is above 0.4. From what I was testing, 0.4-0.8 seems to give an okay result with the realistic checkpoint models.

Tips for generating leg pose:

For simple leg poses, just use prompt and openpose, this Lora should be able to generate that pretty well.

For more complicated leg poses, it's too difficult for the current gen sd, usually you will get bunch of mutant legs and arms, and the heels will turn into a weird shape. For this problem, you may want to use edge detection in the controlnet, like canny, softedge and scribble, the main idea is to use the outline of the picture to keep the overall pose and heels' shape.

  • First, you need to have a reference picture of the desired leg pose with the heels on, then throw it into controlnet

  • Then select the softedge in controlnet then generate a controlnet preview for the picture, and see if the outline of the heels has been detected correctly, if not, you may want to use the canny instead. The outline using canny is more defined than softedge.

  • Then set the controlnet's weight to somewhere between 0.5-1.0 then write your prompt and generate your picture. the lower the weight, the easier to change the background and the clothes, the higher the weight, the better the shape of the pose and heels.

  • If your desired clothes are far different from the reference picture, you can use scribble instead, it leaves more space for the AI to draw the content, but the shape captured is worse comparing the other two.

  • If all three edge-detecting methods failed, you may want to modify the controlnet preview manually to make the outline more clear and remove the unnecessary content. it's pretty simple, just cover the unwanted content with black colour and draw the outline with white colour, even the paint software integrated in windows can do that.

items.description:
Note: there's a LoRA version of this model which generates better faces. Further development of this model will mainly focus on the LoRA for now.

This model generates pictures of women (mainly Asian and Caucasian) wearing beautiful lingerie. Note that the "L" is upper case so not to be confused for a 1.

This model supports most Danbooru tags related to people, women, fashion, lingerie, etc.

Recommended tags:

  • Asian or European. If you specify Asian, you'll get Asian girls. If you specify European, you'll get white girls. If you don't specify either, you might get either or mixed-race girls.

  • bra, panties, underwear, etc: that's the main thing this model is trained to produce.

  • good aesthetic, good quality, good blur, good noise, good contrast - Put any or all of these in your prompt if you want to the image to look better. Note: I've programmatically labeled images this way, similar to how WD1.5 was trained.

  • pntyad: Some of the images were trained on lingerie/panty ads which may result in higher quality images but with a greater possibility of watermarks, text, signatures, and other artifacts appearing. Highly recommended that you add the appropriate negative prompt.

  • (Negative Prompt): poor aesthetic, poor quality, poor blur, poor noise, poor contrast -Put any of these in your negative prompt if your images aren't looking as great.

  • (Negative Prompt): bad-hands-5 - this textual inversion seems to work very well when you're not getting great hands.

  • (Negative Prompt): bad_prompt - similarly, this textual inversion works great when you're not getting properly formed limbs.

  • (Negative Prompt): text, logo, signature, username, watermark - A lot of images in the training set contained logos and watermarks so you'll want these in the negative prompt.

Note that this model seems to work better with upright (512x768) and square images rather than horizontal ones.

items.name: D3fr0
items.description:
Hello again!

Time to bring you another style LORA but a bit different than my previous ones.

This LORA main purpose is to aim to create ice, frozen, cryogenic, etc. in an easy way but it can create diverse styles on your characters or on your prompt. Is NOT designed (again) for landscapes, it's an style adapter/changer.

HOW TO USE IT :

- This time the token "d3fr0" is not necessary since the LORA will work even without it.

- This LORA works even at high values such as 1.3-1.6 due to how it was trained.

- If you feel the ice, freezing, spikes or the "inhuman" appeareance is too high consider to use 0.7-0.8. However if you feel the prompt needs more freeze you can go to 1.3 without problems and 1.5-16 in specific situations.

- The main purpose was to use like "<lora:name:value> portrait/side portrait/fullbody + man/male/woman/female + d3fr0 style but once again you can add a lot in the prompt but the effect tends to go down so if that happens in long and descriptive prompts, try to rise the strenght.

- Even you can use negatives, using negatives feels like you're not getting entire style of the LORA (although fix some things at some seeds).

- Recommended models: I tested with Ghostmix, Colorful, Dreamshaper 3..32, Faetastic, Rev Animated, Dark Sushi Mix... it should work on every model since it's 1.5 based.

THIS LORA IS NOT DESIGNED FOR:

- Landscaping, scenearios, background and anything that it's not icy related.

IMPORTANT!

I wrote an article here and it's like my finetunning diary for the ones interested with releases upcoming, trainings done, exclusive patreon models previews, personal thoughts, etc. So if you want to see what I'm planning or what I'm into, feel free to take a look.

Enjoy and have fun and thanks as always for all your support in our patreon

items.name: Chloe - Hentai University
items.description:
Been busy for a few days. Training for all the HU Loras at this point is done, which is good news. I have a few to retrain already that were trained at a lower resolution, to bring them up to what I've been uploading here, but more than that I just need to find time to actually test/make previews for the last few days of stuff I've made up while work and life has been getting in the way.

I'll upload one of the bois next, but for now...

This is a LoRA for the character Chloe, from Hentai University a game by Noodle Jacuzzi.

Chloe's art is from the artist Pastel Bitch, the set -

Shasei no Oshigoto ~Watashi ga Sukebe ni Shigoite Shabutte Ikasete Ageru~

I've been working my way through making these for all the characters currently in the game, and sharing them in the Discord for HU, but figured I should also put them up here.

In general, I'm working from pretty limited image sets, so expect the results to be a bit wonky at times.

I recommend a weight of around 0.5, possibly lower depending if you're combining the character LoRA with other styles/costumes/etc. along with tagging some defining characteristics of the character you're generating. Higher than that can really push the artist's original style, and may cause you issues.

All characters I train have a "character tag" added into the set to help generate them fairly reliably.

Recommended LoRA Weight - 0.5 for fairly flexible, higher if you want more of the original artist's style, lower if it doesn't play nice with other loras.

Character tag - HUChloe
Recommended tags - purple hair, long hair, pink eyes, medium breasts,

I may have forgotten to check and tag eye color when doing my testing, but hey. If you want it to be "set accurate" be sure to tag.

I've got quite a backlog of these made up already, so I'll be uploading them on and off.

Check my other uploads as I put them out for more HU characters, and if you want any specific character put up soon, let me know.

items.name: Gloria Guida (LoRA)
items.description:
Gloria Guida is one of the main interpreters of the Italian sexy comedies of the seventies, as well as other films mainly with an erotic background. All the images of Gloria that I have used come from her period of activity which goes from 1974 (when she was 19 years old) to 1979.

v0.7 x30batch1 despite 35400 steps (but with Train batch size at 1) is a little undertrained. TE instead seems to me quite well trained. Will retrain this dataset on a Google Colab notebook.. I can't freeze my GPU for 5 hours.

V0.6.4 was trained on a dataset of 59 images mostly from 70's magazine scans and film stills, enhanced with Photo AI, captioned with WD14 then manually edited. In some of the images used, Gloria is completely naked, but is shot from behind. However, her beauty has always been elegant and never obscene. In Italy they had given her the nickname of "queen of showers".

I've recently started using D-adaptation as optimizer, which, although it gives better results, needs more tests to achieve optimal results, so expect at least one more release before v1.0 (I'm a perfectionist). In future versions also I hope to arrange a better dataset.

items.description:
This is a series of LOHA and LORAs of the character Marin Kitagawa from the anime and manga Sono Bisque Doll. It is trained on several outfits and all of her cosplay appearances in the anime.

Marin's LoHA contains several trained outfits, including her school uniform, her bikini, her off shoulder dress, her blue and green flannel shirt, her hoodie, and her kimono. To prompt Marin in her normal uniform, enter "<lora:MarinKitagawa:strength>Marin Kitagawa, school uniform, plaid skirt, black choker". Other outfit prompts include, "flower halterneck bikini, blue and yellow striped shirt, lace choker, string choker, off-shoulder shirt, high-waist skirt, gray jacket, track pants, gray hoodie, kimono". Each of these models can have the "anime screencap" style from the anime when prompted.

Marin's other cosplay outfit LORAs all have their own specific trigger words. Use each respective LORA and their trigger words to prompt them.

For Kuroe Shizuku, enter "Kuroe Shizuku, rose bonnet, black collar, gothic dress, thighhighs".

For Black Lobelia, enter "Black Lobelia, heterochromia, military hat, military jacket, leotard dress, black gloves, black thighhigh boots, black gem".

For Prisoner Veronica, enter "Prisoner Veronica, white belt collar, white belt bra, white shorts, yellow eyes, sharp teeth"

For Liz Kyun, enter "Liz Kyun, frilled crop top, frilled panties, black socks". "wings, tail" are optional.

All of these models were trained on AnythingElsev4.5 at Clip Skip 2. They're very fun to customize, so have fun with them!

items.name: Disco Elysium Character
items.description:
LoRA capable of generating character portraits in the style of Disco Elysium, as close to the originals as possible.

Trained with EveryDream2Trainer on the Lyriel v1.6 model, on 85 Disco Elysium character portraits (100 epochs), each one is out-painted and manually edited to a 512x512 resolution.

Lyriel v1.6+ model is recommended, but it should be compatible with other models.

Use LoRA weight of 2 for more abstract/impressionistic character portraits (think
"Egg Head"), and 1 for something less surreal.

Notes:

  • To strengthen the LoRA: try positives "abstract", "impressionism", and negatives "photo", "3D", "anime"

  • Some models/prompts easily "overweight" the LoRA, so use weight >1 if it seems that it has no effect

  • Keep in mind that default negative prompts destroy LoRA's intentionally imperfect style. That includes textually-inverted negatives, like "easynegative".

All image examples were generated with HiRes-fix, Foolhardy Remacri upscaler, with a 0.4 denoising strength.
